text: Grafton Regis Meadow is a 2 hectare nature reserve east of Grafton Regis in Northamptonshire. It is managed by the Wildlife Trust for Bedfordshire, Cambridgeshire and Northamptonshire. This is a traditionally managed hay meadow on the bank of the Grand Union Canal. Birds visiting the site include curlews, lapwings, long-tailed tits, bullfinches, yellowhammers and wrens. There is no public access to the site. ==References== Category:Wildlife Trust for Bedfordshire, Cambridgeshire and Northamptonshire reserves
